1
00:01:47,039 --> 00:01:48,400
Don't get fooled.

2
00:01:48,800 --> 00:01:49,920
We just found

3
00:01:49,920 --> 00:01:50,720
the second copper frog.

4
00:01:50,720 --> 00:01:51,280
How can there be clues

5
00:01:51,280 --> 00:01:53,000
for the third one so soon?

6
00:01:53,080 --> 00:01:53,940
Professor Wei.

7
00:01:54,320 --> 00:01:55,039
Just you wait.

8
00:01:55,039 --> 00:01:56,560
I'll make you accept it when I

9
00:01:56,560 --> 00:01:58,039
bring a girlfriend home.

10
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:02,800
What's wrong?

11
00:02:03,360 --> 00:02:04,820
Is something on your mind?

12
00:02:05,440 --> 00:02:07,770
Compared to this thousand-year slumber,

13
00:02:07,800 --> 00:02:09,060
I'm more interested in

14
00:02:09,360 --> 00:02:10,960
the journey you've taken.

15
00:02:16,120 --> 00:02:17,850
If immortality really exists,

16
00:02:18,400 --> 00:02:19,560
how does one resolve

17
00:02:21,360 --> 00:02:23,160
a thousand years of loneliness?

18
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:24,880
This girl...

19
00:02:25,280 --> 00:02:27,610
asking about my dating history like that.

20
00:02:27,800 --> 00:02:29,800
Good thing I follow some public accounts,

21
00:02:29,800 --> 00:02:30,640
or else

22
00:02:30,640 --> 00:02:32,370
I would've been tricked by her.

23
00:02:32,440 --> 00:02:35,040
Immortality isn't about the body never dying,

24
00:02:35,079 --> 00:02:37,010
but about endless reincarnation.

25
00:02:37,600 --> 00:02:38,660
My thousand years,

26
00:02:38,760 --> 00:02:40,520
ten lifetimes of reincarnation,

27
00:02:40,520 --> 00:02:41,720
have finally come to fruition

28
00:02:41,720 --> 00:02:42,640
in this moment.

29
00:02:55,040 --> 00:02:55,700
We're here.

30
00:02:57,960 --> 00:03:01,290
Because my parents helped Professor Wei with excavations,

31
00:03:01,600 --> 00:03:03,400
I hardly saw them all year round.

32
00:03:04,960 --> 00:03:06,490
I was just a child back then.

33
00:03:07,480 --> 00:03:09,280
My classmates all laughed at me.

34
00:03:09,920 --> 00:03:11,320
They said I was an orphan.

35
00:03:13,080 --> 00:03:14,040
With no parents.

36
00:03:15,600 --> 00:03:17,079
Even for parent-teacher meetings,

37
00:03:17,079 --> 00:03:18,940
my neighbors had to attend for me.

38
00:03:20,880 --> 00:03:21,680
Later,

39
00:03:22,280 --> 00:03:23,480
I remember when Professor Wei

40
00:03:23,480 --> 00:03:25,540
was searching for Buluotuo's Tears,

41
00:03:25,920 --> 00:03:26,720
he failed.

42
00:03:27,320 --> 00:03:28,920
The whole team disbanded.

43
00:03:29,920 --> 00:03:30,800
I thought my parents could finally

44
00:03:30,800 --> 00:03:32,060
come home to be with me.

45
00:03:33,120 --> 00:03:34,040
But while searching for

46
00:03:34,040 --> 00:03:35,240
Buluotuo's Tears,

47
00:03:36,400 --> 00:03:38,060
after they left that one time,

48
00:03:40,160 --> 00:03:42,020
they were never heard from again.

49
00:03:43,079 --> 00:03:44,760
It turns out that in every life,

50
00:03:44,760 --> 00:03:46,960
he has to suffer the pain of separation.

51
00:03:50,360 --> 00:03:51,880
Although there are many things

52
00:03:51,880 --> 00:03:53,610
that I can't clearly remember,

53
00:03:54,040 --> 00:03:55,880
the feeling of having someone important

54
00:03:55,880 --> 00:03:57,600
torn away from your side...

55
00:03:59,120 --> 00:04:00,280
I know that feeling.

56
00:04:02,280 --> 00:04:04,280
No matter what happened in the past,

57
00:04:04,480 --> 00:04:06,480
fate has brought us together again.

58
00:04:06,680 --> 00:04:08,740
Whether it is retrieving my memories

59
00:04:09,040 --> 00:04:11,040
or searching for Buluotuo's Tears,

60
00:04:11,320 --> 00:04:13,120
I hope that on the journey ahead,

61
00:04:13,280 --> 00:04:14,160
you can see me as

62
00:04:14,160 --> 00:04:15,490
someone you can rely on.

63
00:04:16,440 --> 00:04:17,600
So the reason she refused to admit

64
00:04:17,600 --> 00:04:19,200
that she is from modern times

65
00:04:19,200 --> 00:04:20,480
was to use her identity as a Princess

66
00:04:20,480 --> 00:04:22,140
to confess her feelings to me.

67
00:04:29,360 --> 00:04:30,240
It's time.

68
00:04:31,680 --> 00:04:32,520
Time for what?

69
00:04:39,159 --> 00:04:40,560
Where the Frog God points

70
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:42,800
is where the third bronze frog lies.

71
00:04:56,600 --> 00:04:57,400
Found it.

72
00:05:01,440 --> 00:05:02,240
Back then,

73
00:05:02,720 --> 00:05:04,760
we used the bronze frog to reflect the moonlight,

74
00:05:04,760 --> 00:05:06,160
fought off the pursuers,

75
00:05:06,280 --> 00:05:07,940
and managed to escape safely.

76
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:10,800
Are you sure

77
00:05:11,080 --> 00:05:12,740
this is the third bronze frog?

78
00:05:13,200 --> 00:05:14,120
To me,

79
00:05:14,480 --> 00:05:15,920
it just looks like a rock.

80
00:05:15,920 --> 00:05:18,000
Are you sure you didn't grab the wrong thing?

81
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:19,800
This is the testament to our love.

82
00:05:19,800 --> 00:05:21,120
How could you forget?

83
00:05:22,920 --> 00:05:23,720
Princess.

84
00:05:24,280 --> 00:05:25,560
The testament to our love

85
00:05:25,560 --> 00:05:27,320
has never been these inanimate objects.

86
00:05:27,320 --> 00:05:28,760
Not these four bronze frogs,

87
00:05:28,760 --> 00:05:30,160
nor the Tears of Bulotuo.

88
00:05:30,240 --> 00:05:32,370
It is everything we have been through.

89
00:05:33,680 --> 00:05:35,540
The adventures we took together.

90
00:05:44,280 --> 00:05:45,740
The high-fives we shared.

91
00:05:51,080 --> 00:05:52,600
And how we tried every way

92
00:05:52,760 --> 00:05:54,080
to trick the Tiger Marquis.

93
00:05:54,080 --> 00:05:54,920
An expert.

94
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:57,730
Tiger Marquis is indeed an expert.

95
00:05:58,240 --> 00:05:58,960
Prince,

96
00:05:59,080 --> 00:06:01,160
Tiger Marquis has passed your test.

97
00:06:01,160 --> 00:06:03,280
You don't have to worry about my safety anymore.

98
00:06:03,280 --> 00:06:04,320
Here we are,

99
00:06:04,600 --> 00:06:05,930
meeting unexpectedly.

100
00:06:06,760 --> 00:06:07,560
It is you.

101
00:06:08,640 --> 00:06:09,440
These things

102
00:06:09,920 --> 00:06:11,600
are the true testament to our love.

103
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:12,160
Love.

104
00:06:12,400 --> 00:06:13,260
It is just love.

105
00:06:14,040 --> 00:06:15,170
Regardless of time,

106
00:06:15,720 --> 00:06:16,980
regardless of status,

107
00:06:17,360 --> 00:06:20,220
and certainly regardless of that useless history.

108
00:06:26,120 --> 00:06:26,920
Princess,

109
00:06:27,480 --> 00:06:28,480
what's wrong?

110
00:06:31,720 --> 00:06:32,800
I am the princess.

111
00:06:33,040 --> 00:06:33,480
No, no.

112
00:06:33,960 --> 00:06:35,880
I am the princess you think I am.

113
00:06:37,640 --> 00:06:39,570
What new trick are you playing now?

114
00:06:49,960 --> 00:06:50,720
Yuwen Ying.

115
00:06:50,880 --> 00:06:51,720
What are you doing?

116
00:06:51,720 --> 00:06:52,980
How is your girl doing?

117
00:06:53,360 --> 00:06:54,090
(Thai) Fool.

118
00:06:54,320 --> 00:06:55,720
(Thai) You've been used.

119
00:06:55,720 --> 00:06:56,920
Aya is mine alone.

120
00:06:57,120 --> 00:06:58,650
(Thai) If you show up again,

121
00:06:58,800 --> 00:06:59,760
(Thai) I will kill you.
